# Architecture

## Folder Structure

```
app/                          # Routes, layouts, pages only
features/{module}/
  actions.ts                  # Server Actions (mutations)
  service.ts                  # Business logic
  queries.ts                  # Read-only Supabase queries
  schema.ts                   # Zod schemas (shared client + server)
  types.ts                    # Module-specific types
  components/                 # Feature-scoped UI
components/ui/                # shadcn primitives
lib/
  supabase/client.ts          # Browser client
  supabase/server.ts          # Server Component / Action client
  supabase/admin.ts           # Service-role (server-only)
  auth/                       # requireUser, requireRole helpers
```

## Module Rules

- A feature module owns its schema, types, queries, service, and actions
- Cross-feature imports go through the service/query layer — never import another feature's components directly
- Shared utilities belong in `lib/`, not duplicated across features

## Adding a New Feature

1. Create `features/{name}/` with `schema.ts`, `types.ts`, `queries.ts`, `service.ts`, `actions.ts`
2. Add route under `app/` that calls queries (reads) and passes data to components
3. Components call actions (writes) — never Supabase directly
